  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What do we call video with words on it?",
  "response": "The term for a video that includes words displayed on the screen can vary depending on the context and purpose of the text. Here are some common terms used:\n\n1. **Subtitled Video**:\n   - **Definition**: Videos that display translated or transcribed dialogue at the bottom of the screen.\n   - **Use Case**: Often used for foreign films or to provide accessibility for hearing-impaired viewers.\n\n2. **Captioned Video**:\n   - **Definition**: Similar to subtitles, but captions often include additional information like sound effects, speaker identification, and other audio cues.\n   - **Use Case**: Primarily used to make videos accessible to the deaf or hard of hearing.\n\n3. **Lyric Video**:\n   - **Definition**: A music video that displays the song's lyrics in sync with the music.\n   - **Use Case**: Commonly used by artists to promote new singles, allowing fans to learn and sing along with the song.\n\n4. **Kinetic Typography Video**:\n   - **Definition**: A type of animation that focuses on the expressive movement of text to convey emotions or emphasize certain parts of the message.\n   - **Use Case**: Often used in marketing, explainer videos, or artistic projects to make the text more engaging.\n\n5. **Text-Based Video or Typographic Video**:\n   - **Definition**: Videos where text is the main visual element, sometimes accompanied by minimal or no additional graphics.\n   - **Use Case**: Used for storytelling, conveying quotes, or presenting information in a visually appealing way.\n\n6. **Video with On-Screen Text Overlay**:\n   - **Definition**: Any video that includes text superimposed over the visuals, which can serve various purposes like highlighting key points, providing context, or adding commentary.\n   - **Use Case**: Common in tutorials, vlogs, and instructional videos to enhance understanding.\n\n7. **Animated Text Video**:\n   - **Definition**: Videos that incorporate animated text elements to create dynamic and visually interesting content.\n   - **Use Case**: Used in advertisements, social media posts, and creative projects to capture viewers' attention.\n\n**Choosing the Right Term**:\n- If you're referring to translations or transcriptions of spoken dialogue, \"subtitled\" or \"captioned\" are appropriate.\n- If the text is the main visual component or is used creatively to convey a message, terms like \"lyric video,\" \"kinetic typography,\" or \"text-based video\" might be more suitable.\n\nUnderstanding the specific purpose and presentation of the text within the video will help you select the most accurate term.",
